\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. O. amethystea} Thuill.,{\i  Fl. Paris} ed. 2, 317 (1800). Leaves linear-lanceolate to -oblong, acute. Bracts 12-22 mm. Calyx 9-15 mm; segments unequally bidentate or entire. Corolla 15-25 mm, sparsely glandular-pubescent, white or cream, usually tinged with violet, pink or brown distally; lobes of lower lip subequal. Filaments inserted 3-4 mm above base of corolla. Stigma purple or yellow.{\i  On various dicotyledonous herbs. S., W. & W.C. Europe northwards to S. England.} Al Br Bu Co Ga Ge Gr He Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   (a) Subsp.{\b  amethystea} (incl. {\i O. attica} Reuter): Calyx-segments 1-veined, filiform above. Corolla often inflected near base, more or less straight above, usually tinged with violet; upper lip deeply 2-lobed. Stigma purple or yellow. {\i Usually on species of }Eryngium, Daucus, Ballota{\i  and Compositae. Throughout the range of the species}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   (b) Subsp. castellana (Reuter) Rouy, {\i Fl. Fr.}{\b  11}: 185 (1909) ({\i O. castellana} Reuter): Calyx-segments 3- to 4-veined, not filiform. Corolla uniformly curved throughout, usually tinged with pink or brown; upper lip entire to 2-lobed. Stigma purple.{\i  Usually on} Digitalis{\i  spp. S.W. Europe}.
\par

