\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. O. canescens} C. Presl in J. & C. Presl, {\i Del. Prag.} 72 (1822). Leaves ovate. Bracts 10-20 mm. Calyx 8-16 mm; segments usually unequally bifid. Corolla 12-18 mm, glandular-pubescent to subglabrous, yellow tinged with red; upper lip emarginate or 2-lobed; lower lip with subequal lobes. Filaments inserted 3-4·5 mm above base of corolla. Stigma yellow.{\i  On Compositae and perhaps other plants. C. & E. parts of Mediterranean region.} Co Cr Gr It Sa Si.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. O. esulae} Pancic,{\i  Fl. Princ. Serb. Addit.} 194 (1884). Bracts 10-12 mm. Calyx 7-9 mm; segments entire or variably bifid. Corolla (12-)15-18 mm, glandular-pubescent, yellow, tinged with brown or purple distally; upper lip 2-lobed; lower lip with the middle lobe the largest. Filaments inserted (4-)5-6 mm above base of corolla. Stigma yellow. {\i On} Euphorbia esula. •{\i  E. Jugoslavia, C. & S. Bulgaria.} Bu Ju.
\par
 
